<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-cGZCLeL9fAHU-E4Jp4CvPw" name=",_vTe84J5vEeCHFd5_MqJHKQ" guid="-cGZCLeL9fAHU-E4Jp4CvPw" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This task is based upon the safety analysis of the HW element and the&amp;nbsp;impact of actions such as assembly,&#xD;
    disassembly, decommissioning operations and maintenance on the safety concept.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If such safety-related special characteristics are identified verification measures for production and operation should&#xD;
    be specified along with acceptance criteria for those measures.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Full traceability to the safety-related hardware element shall also be maintained.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For a detailed understanding of the requirements for production and operation it is advised that the user refer to ISO&#xD;
    26262, volume 5, clause 7.5.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <purpose>To Specify the safety requirements that could cause errors caused by assembly, disassembly and maintenance for example.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
